<paragraph id="8B826773BE46FFD6FF6D55D3235DED1C" blockId="106.[151,1436,626,1172]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FEDB55D320B4EC84" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[368,659,666,692]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FEDB55D32011EC83" box="[368,566,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Luciola obsoleta</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
were incorrectly identified by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FBAC55D3269FEC84" author="Haneda, Y." box="[1031,1208,666,692]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="4 - 10" refId="ref104816" refString="Haneda, Y. (1966) Synchronous Flashing of Fireflies in New Guinea. Science Report of the Yokosuka City Museum No. 12, 4 - 10." type="book chapter" year="1966">Haneda (1966)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FB4F55D327BBEC84" box="[1252,1436,666,692]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FB4F55D32755EC83" box="[1252,1394,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FF34558B2351ECEC" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[159,374,706,732]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="171 - 188" refId="ref102796" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 b) Lucioline Morphology, Taxonomy and Behaviour: A Reappraisal. (Coleoptera, Lampyridae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 113, 171 - 188." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne 1987b</bibRefCitation>
). This genus has not been recorded from New 
<collectingCountry id="F32A27E3BE46FFD6FC0B558B21DFECEC" box="[928,1016,706,732]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Guinea</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FBAE558B26FEECEC" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[1029,1241,706,732]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="103 - 139" refId="ref102712" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1968) Revisional Studies of Australian and Indomalayan Luciolini (Coleoptera, Lampyridae, Luciolinae). University of Queensland Papers, Department of Entomology, University of Queensland Press II no 6, 103 - 139." type="journal article" year="1968">Ballantyne (1968)</bibRefCitation>
described a single unusual New Guinean female, which she tentatively assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FC1F55A32666ED33" box="[948,1089,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FC1F55A32666ED33" box="[948,1089,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This female is assigned here to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FF1E545B2307ED1B" authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2009" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2009" box="[181,288,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Missimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FF1E545B2307ED1B" box="[181,288,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Missimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FE83545B235DED1C" bold="true" box="[296,378,786,812]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A061ABE46FFD6FE83545B235DED1C" box="[296,378,786,812]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B826773BE46FFD6FF6C5473266CEAA4" blockId="106.[151,1436,626,1172]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FF6C54732372ED63" box="[199,341,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FF6C54732372ED63" box="[199,341,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described for a single species, 
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FCA254732179ED63" box="[777,862,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FCA25473217DED63" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[777,858,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylifer">stylifer</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
possessing unusual modifications to abdominal ventrite 7 and T8 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FEC6542B203BED4C" author="Wittmer, W." box="[365,540,866,892]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="21 - 24" refId="ref107799" refString="Wittmer, W., (1939) Fauna Buruana. Coleoptera 7. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der indo-malayischen Malacodermata. Treubia, 17, 21 - 24, 127 (Lampyridae)." type="journal article" year="1939">Wittmer, 1939</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FD9B542B212AED4C" author="McDermott, F. A." box="[560,781,866,892]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="98 - 118" refId="ref106386" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae Pars. 9. Coleopterorum Catalogus (Junk-Schenkling) (Ed. Sec), 1 - 149 (Luciolini, 98 - 118)." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FC29542B2637ED4B" box="[898,1040,866,891]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FC29542B2637ED4B" box="[898,1040,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FB75542B2718ED4B" box="[1246,1343,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FB75542B271CED4B" box="[1246,1339,866,891]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Luciola</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FAEE542B2304ED94" author="Ballantyne, L. A." pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="103 - 139" refId="ref102712" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1968) Revisional Studies of Australian and Indomalayan Luciolini (Coleoptera, Lampyridae, Luciolinae). University of Queensland Papers, Department of Entomology, University of Queensland Press II no 6, 103 - 139." type="journal article" year="1968">Ballantyne (1968)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the subgenus, keyed and described four species (two of them new), and assigned 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FF3C54FB23E5EDFC" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[151,450,946,972]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamulata">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FF3C54FB234FEDFB" box="[151,360,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Luciola hamulata</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FE4154FB205FEDFB" box="[490,632,946,971]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FE4154FB205FEDFB" box="[490,632,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FD2C54FB21DFEDFC" author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R." box="[647,1016,946,972]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="223 - 305" refId="ref103236" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R. (1970) Revisional studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae: Luciolini). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 96, 223 - 305." type="journal article" year="1970">Ballantyne and McLean (1970)</bibRefCitation>
figured aspects of the morphology. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FF3C5493235EEDC4" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[151,377,986,1012]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="171 - 188" refId="ref102796" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 b) Lucioline Morphology, Taxonomy and Behaviour: A Reappraisal. (Coleoptera, Lampyridae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 113, 171 - 188." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987b)</bibRefCitation>
described certain presumed sexual characters of certain species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FB205493273EEDC3" box="[1163,1305,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FB205493273EEDC3" box="[1163,1305,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(eg curved legs, and terminal abdomen structure) and suggested uses in a reproductive context. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FBD2534B22C3EA74" author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C." pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="363 - 377" refId="ref103129" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2001) A new firefly, Luciola (Pygoluciola) kinabalua sp. n. (Coleoptera: Lampyridae), from Malaysia, with observations on a possible copulation clamp. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 49 (2), 363 - 377." type="journal article" year="2001">Ballantyne and Lambkin (2001)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species and (2006) reassigned 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D1CF0BE46FFD6FCB65363218CEA73" box="[797,939,1066,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949BB61BE46FFD6FCB65363218CEA73" box="[797,939,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to generic status based on representatives from Borneo only. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FED6531B2074EA5C" author="Ballantyne, L." box="[381,595,1106,1132]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref102993" refString="Ballantyne, L. A (2008) Pygoluciola satoi, a new species of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae) from the Philippines. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 56 (1), 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2008">Ballantyne (2008)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species from the 
<collectingCountry id="F32A27E3BE46FFD6FC53531B2658EA5C" box="[1016,1151,1106,1132]" name="Philippines" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC1A82BE46FFD6FB6A531B22C3EAA4" author="Fu, X. H. &amp; Ballantyne, L. A." pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref104435" refString="Fu, X. H. &amp; Ballantyne, L. A. (2008) Taxonomy and behaviour of lucioline fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae) with redefinition and new species of Pygoluciola Wittmer from mainland China and review of Luciola LaPorte. Zootaxa 1733, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2008">Fu and Ballantyne (2008)</bibRefCitation>
a new species from mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F32A27E3BE46FFD6FDE2533320B5EAA4" box="[585,658,1146,1172]" name="China" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">China</collectingCountry>
, and an extended generic description.
</paragraph>
